<body>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard personal data when children under 18 years old use the "Fast Facts Math" mobile application (the "App").</p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We do not collect any personal data from children using the App. We do not require users to provide any personally identifiable information such as names, addresses, email addresses, or phone numbers.</p>

    <h2>Use of Google Firebase</h2>
    <p>We use Google Firebase for crash tracking and analytics purposes. This service may collect certain non-personal information automatically, including device information, app usage data, and crash reports. The data collected by Google Firebase is used to improve the performance, stability, and user experience of the App. Please refer to Google's Privacy Policy for more information on how Google handles this data: <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>.</p>

    <h2>Parental Consent</h2>
    <p>We strongly recommend that parents or legal guardians supervise their children while using the App. If you become aware that your child has provided us with personal information without your consent, please contact us immediately so that we can remove such information from our records.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to update or change our Privacy Policy at any time. Any updates or changes will be reflected on this page, and we encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically.</p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or the App, please contact us at mitchellmarkteacher@gmail.com.</p>
</body>
